truenas-pylibvirt (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add nsexec subpackage for entering a running libvirt-LXC container as
    a child process with the container's configured capability restrictions
    applied to the final exec. Sanctioned entry point is
    `python3 -m truenas_pylibvirt.nsexec`; direct use of the C primitives
    from a persistent multi-threaded daemon is unsafe (see module docstring).
  * Ship a C extension (truenas_pylibvirt.nsexec._native) linked against
    libcap, exposing setns, drop_bounding, cap_from_name, cap_to_name,
    cap_max_bits, cap_set_proc_from_text, the CLONE_NEW* constants, and
    the composite enter_and_exec entry point. enter_and_exec takes
    caller-supplied namespace fds (user_fd plus a list[int] of other fds),
    switches the non-user namespaces first via setns(fd, 0) then the user
    namespace, applies bounding-set drops (prctl(PR_CAPBSET_DROP)), applies
    the explicit effective+permitted capability set (capset(2)), forks so
    the exec'd shell lands in the target's PID namespace, assumes container
    root in the child (setgroups/setgid/setuid) so writes to idmapped
    mounts translate correctly, and relays the child's exit status.
  * Namespace fds are obtained via libvirt (virDomainLxcOpenNamespace,
    exposed in Python as libvirt_lxc.lxcOpenNamespace) instead of opening
    /proc/<pid>/ns/<kind> directly, removing the PID-reuse race between
    lookup and setns.
  * ALL_CAPABILITIES is enumerated at import time from libcap
    (cap_max_bits + cap_to_name) rather than hand-maintained, so upgrading
    libcap/kernel picks up new capability names without source edits.
  * Export DEFAULT_CONTAINERS_URI and DEFAULT_VMS_URI from the top-level
    package; DomainManagers defaults now reference these constants.
  * Package is architecture-specific (was arch: all). Add libcap-dev to
    Build-Depends.

 -- TrueNAS Engineering <dev@truenas.com>  Fri, 24 Apr 2026 10:00:00 -0500

